      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is the most logical approach because it respects the democratic will of the people who ratified the Constitution, ensuring that judges do not impose their own modern policy preferences under the guise of interpretation. By anchoring meaning to the text at the time of adoption, originalism prevents the judiciary from acting as a super-legislature that can rewrite the fundamental law to suit contemporary political agendas. This method maintains the separation of powers by strictly limiting the Court's role to interpreting the fixed rules the Founders established, rather than creating new rights or obligations. Ultimately, it offers a stable, predictable framework for governance that protects minority rights by constraining majority tyranny through the written law itself.",
